wn&amp;rft.btitle=Honorary+Degrees+Awarded+by+Oglethorpe+University&amp;rft.pub=Oglethorpe+University&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.oglethorpe.edu%2Fabout_us%2Fhistory%2Fhonorary_degrees.asp&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AKarl+Haas\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-WashingtonPost-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-WashingtonPost_5-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-WashingtonPost_5-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-WashingtonPost_5-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-WashingtonPost_5-3\"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Holley, Joe (2005-02-08). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/articles/A6475-2005Feb7.html\">\"Classical Radio Personality Karl Haas, 91, Dies\"</a>. <i>The Washington Post</i>. p.&#160;B06<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2008-11-17</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Classical+Radio+Personality+Karl+Haas%2C+91%2C+Dies&amp;rft.pages=B06&amp;rft.pub=%27%27The+Washington+Post%27%27&amp;rft.date=2005-02-08&amp;rft.aulast=Holley&amp;rft.aufirst=Joe&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fwp-dyn%2Farticles%2FA6475-2005Feb7.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AKarl+Haas\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-family-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-family_6-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Symons, Craig (2005-02-07). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.choralnet.org/view/169203\">\"Rest In Peace Karl Haas\"</a>. <i>American Choral Directors Association</i